#!/usr/bin/env ssc
---
name: fs-confined
description: std.fs.resolveWithin lexical path confinement (M10) — rejects `..`/absolute escapes
---

# Confined filesystem paths

`resolveWithin(root, rel)` lexically resolves `rel` under `root`, returning `None`
when `rel` would escape via `..` or an absolute path. Symlinks are not resolved.

[resolveWithin](std/fs.ssc)

```scalascript
def show(rel: String): Unit =
  resolveWithin("/srv/data", rel) match
    case Some(p) => println("ok: " + rel + " -> " + p)
    case None    => println("blocked: " + rel)

show("a/b.txt")
show("a/./b.txt")
show("a/../b.txt")
show("a/b/../c")
show("x/y/z/../../w")
show("sub/dir/f")
show("../etc/passwd")
show("a/../../etc/passwd")
show("/etc/passwd")
```
